item.title: 8542 El Paseo Grande
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
On a uniquely prominent site on an exceptionally exclusive stretch above the sands on La Jolla Shores beach, this 9,000sf manse maximizes its 50' of beach frontage and panoramic views with vast walls of disappearing glass for seamless indoor-outdoor enjoyment of the wondrous marine environment. Designed for sublime privacy with minimal maintenance, the residence offers full view of surf, sea, sunsets, migrating wildlife and action on the beach below. Please see supplement.

Designed with clean, contemporary lines and massive planes introducing the importance of its structure and site, this home was designed to invite spectacular ever-changing views inside via grand walls of glass and expansive outdoor terrace decking. Fittingly, the sea is the focal point while living areas, luxurious and voluminous, were designed with sensitive simplicity. An elevator serves each of the three levels of the home, and the master occupies an entire floor with two baths, fireplace, spa tubs, and spacious separate closets. Two additional bedrooms suites and an office/optional fourth bedroom welcome family and friends. The main level kitchen is a chef's pleasure with slab granite countertops, dual dishwashers, separate prep sink, double refrigerators, double oven, and center island.

The huge recreation room with fireplace and full bath features another complete kitchen and bar with birdseye maple cabinetry, sink, dishwasher, wine cooler and countertops servicing the game area. A separate laundry room with chute from master closet, pet shower, and extensive storage opens to a private patio. Buyer to verify square footage and all information prior to close of escrow.

item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!
